text: Life is just a senseless act followed by random stuff then you die and nobody remembers you. The joke is when you acknowledge this you either go mental or blank. I wish I can go blank. I wish I could be happy.
When life is going nowhere, maybe you can just take a train and live like Kerouac in the 60s. I'll just miss my cats. I asked if they wanted to come and they just said no.
I wish I was in Mexico city right now.
Sometimes you think you can fill the void with random stuff like food, sex, self-indulgent stuff, but at the end, the void inside you ends up eating your mind.
